						               													<description>Similar to Ratz-Fatz, this is a collection of game ideas and materials. The box contains 50 wooden figures (mostly animals, but also a train, truck, pirate etc.), 4 little metal suitcases, a die, a game book and a CD with stories and a song.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Basic idea: The wooden figures are placed on the table. While a story, poem or riddle is being read (or played from the CD), the players have to listen closely. When an object from the table is mentioned or the solution to a riddle, the players have to grab it. The player who has collected the most figures at the end of the text wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Variants include just putting the figures into the box after they were mentioned (non-competitive play) and a memory variant in which objects that were put away before the game have to be called out when mentioned in the story.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
